##Phishing Attacks

#### Look through Marcus's emails below and see which ones might be legit and which might be phishing attacks.

<div style="font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6;">


  <hr>

  <p><strong>Message A – Text</strong></p>
  <p>
    Hey Marcus — Coach D here. The sports store’s got a deal for team players on new sneakers.<br><br>
    You’ll need your school ID and cell for the discount code.<br><br>
    Want me to add you to the list?
  </p>

  <hr>

  <p><strong>Message B – Email</strong></p>
  <p><em>Subject:</em> <strong>Colorado DMV Action Required – Learner’s Permit Suspension Notice</strong></p>
  <p>
    Dear Marcus Lee,<br><br>
    Our system shows that your learner’s permit file is incomplete. If we don’t receive verification within 72 hours, your permit will be automatically suspended.<br><br>
    To avoid interruption, please log in to your DMV profile and confirm your info:<br>
    <a href="#">dmv.colorado.gov-verify.info</a><br><br>
    Sincerely,<br>
    Colorado DMV Processing Center
  </p>

  <hr>

  <p><strong>Message C – Instagram DM</strong></p>
  <p>
    <strong>From: @JordanDenverSneaks</strong><br><br>
    Hey Marcus! We’re giving away early access passes to the Air Jordan Retro Drop in Denver this Saturday!<br><br>
    To confirm you’re 16+, we just need your full name, birthdate, and cell.<br><br>
    Spots are limited and going fast — reply by tonight to lock it in!
  </p>

</div>

##Breach Reports 
####A data breach is a security incident where sensitive, confidential, or private information is accessed, disclosed, or stolen by unauthorized individuals.

#### Look through Marcus's breach report to try to determine what happened and what type of password attack your user was vulnerable to.

<div style="font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6;">

  <h3 style="color: #00838f;">Breach Report</h3>
  <p><strong>Service Breached:</strong> CourtCast Sports Streaming<br>
     <strong>Login Location:</strong> Dallas, TX<br>
     <strong>Time of Access:</strong> 11:42 p.m.<br>
     <strong>AI Analysis:</strong> Time and device usage consistent with late-night mobile logins on previous dates.
  </p>

  <p>Account activity followed a sneaker promotion post by the service.<br>
     The login was successful on the first attempt from an Android phone using mobile data.<br>
     The password used was: <strong>FreshKicks23</strong>
  </p>

  <p><strong>AI Analysis:</strong> Password found in 2023 breach dataset associated with sneaker resale site.<br>
     No password changes had been made since that breach.<br>
     The attacker viewed saved payment settings but made no purchases.<br>
     <strong>AI Analysis:</strong> User's account had not been updated with a profile photo or linked payment method since signup.
  </p>

  <br>

  <h3 style="color: #00838f;">Password Attacks</h3>

  <table style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; border:1px solid #ccc; font-size: 15px;">
    <tr>
      <td style="font-weight:bold; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">Credential stuffing attack</td>
      <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">
        When attackers use real usernames and passwords (often from past breaches) to break into other accounts.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="font-weight:bold; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">Password guessing attack</td>
      <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">
        When attackers try different passwords for one account, hoping to guess the right one.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="font-weight:bold; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">Password spraying attack</td>
      <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">
        When an attacker tries one common password on many different accounts to avoid detection.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="font-weight:bold; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">Brute force attack</td>
      <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">
        When an attacker rapidly tries a large number of possible passwords on one account, using automated tools to find the correct one.
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>

</div>

